Sentencas: The thickness of an ultrathin blocking layer for anodic aluminum oxide (AAO)-supported thin-film solid oxide fuel cells is determined.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate

Sentencas: The atomic layer-deposited (ALD) ultrathin yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) blocking layer for gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) electrolyte cell is deposited on 300 nm-thick Pt anode-coated AAO substrates.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate

Sentencas: The surface of AAO substrates is examined to be non-uniform in terms of pore size and bump inclination by field emission scanning electron microscopic analysis.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate

Sentencas: While the average pore size is 130 nm, the pore size ranges from 36 to 207 nm.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate

Sentencas: While the average slope angle is 42 degrees, the slope angle ranges from 9 degrees to 79 degrees.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate

Sentencas: A growth modelling result considering the pore sizes and the slope angles presents that highly reliable ALD-deposited YSZ blocking layers need to be thicker than 93 nm.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate

Sentencas: This prediction well corresponds to the evolution of open circuit voltages for 400 nm-thick GDC electrolyte cells with 60 nm-thick and 120 nm-thick ALD-deposited YSZ blocking layers.
Titulo: Thickness Determination of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Blocking Layer Prepared by Atomic Layer Deposition Considering the Non-uniform Surface Geometry of Porous Substrate
